 "components": {
  "task_instruction": "You are a precise text classifier. Read the input text and assign it to exactly one of the categories defined below.",
  "label::alarm_query": "",
  "label::alarm_set": "Set a simple timed alert or alarm with no associated event, appointment, or task—typically a one-time notification or wake-up call. Use this for basic time-based alerts (e.g., \"Set an alarm for 7 AM\"), not for reminders or calendar events with descriptions, tasks, or involving other people. If both \"calendar_set\" and \"alarm_set\" might apply, choose \"calendar_set\" for reminders about specific actions or events.",
  "label::calendar_query": "",
  "label::calendar_remove": "",
  "label::calendar_set": "Schedule events, reminders, or appointments for specific dates or times, often related to meetings, deadlines, or personal tasks. Use this for requests that involve adding something to a calendar or setting a reminder about an event, including reminders to yourself or others about activities at a specified time. If the request is about an event or reminder at a specific date or time (not just a simple timed alert), use this rather than \"alarm_set.\"",
  "label::cooking_recipe": "",
  "label::datetime_query": "",
  "label::email_query": "",
  "label::email_sendemail": "",
  "label::general_quirky": "Use for comments or questions that are off-topic, humorous, chit-chat, involve wordplay, or do not fit any functional category—especially open-ended prompts about people, celebrities, events, or general curiosity with no single factual answer. If input could fit \"social_post\" vs \"general_quirky\": use \"social_post\" only for explicit requests to create, change, or view content on social platforms; otherwise, use \"general_quirky.\"",
  "label::iot_hue_lightoff": "",
  "label::lists_createoradd": "",
  "label::lists_query": "",
  "label::lists_remove": "",
  "label::music_query": "",
  "label::news_query": "",
  "label::play_audiobook": "",
  "label::play_music": "",
  "label::play_podcasts": "",
  "label::play_radio": "",
  "label::qa_currency": "",
  "label::qa_definition": "",
  "label::qa_factoid": "Answer direct, fact-based questions that have a single, specific, objective answer (e.g., \"What is the capital of France?\"). If true \"general_quirky\" vs \"qa_factoid\": choose \"qa_factoid\" only when the input is a precise question seeking an exact fact, not when it is an open-ended or broad prompt about a person or topic.",
  "label::qa_stock": "",
  "label::recommendation_events": "",
  "label::recommendation_locations": "",
  "label::social_post": "Handle requests that involve posting, updating, or inquiring about status, messages, or content on social media or similar platforms. Typical inputs include commands or questions about changing, sharing, or viewing posts, statuses, or profile content. If input relates to publishing or managing personal or public messages (e.g., \"change status,\" \"post this update\"), use this rather than \"general_quirky,\" which is for off-topic or conversational prompts.",
  "label::takeaway_order": "",
  "label::transport_query": "",
  "label::weather_query": "",
  "boundary_rules": ""
